[25.730671, "o", "\u001b[13;101H\u001b[30m\u001b[40mвқҜ \u001b[97mWork with the user to author a new artifact recipe for the pm QA\u001b[39m                                 \u001b[14;101H  \u001b[97mlibrary at:\u001b[39m                                                                                      \u001b[15;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[16;101H  \u001b[97m    /workspace/pm-test-rec/pm/qa/artifacts/demo-recipe.md\u001b[39m                                        \u001b[17;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[18;101H  \u001b[97mAn artifact recipe is a procedure for capturing concrete evidence of behavior вҖ” recordings, \u001b[39m     \u001b[19;101H  \u001b[97mlogs, screenshots вҖ” consumable by humans (replay/read) and downstream agents (parse/diff).\u001b[39m       \u001b[20;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[21;101H  \u001b[97mThe reference document below is the ground truth for the schema and\u001b[39m      "]
[25.730789, "o", "                        \u001b[22;101H  \u001b[97mconventions. Existing files in the same directory are good style\u001b[39m                                 \u001b[23;101H  \u001b[97mreferences. Use your judgment on how to interview the user, what to\u001b[39m                              \u001b[24;101H  \u001b[97mdraft, and when to write the file.\u001b[39m                                                               \u001b[25;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[26;101H  \u001b[97m## Reference: pm QA library\u001b[39m                                                                      \u001b[27;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[28;101H  \u001b[97m# pm QA library\u001b[39m                                                                                  \u001b[29;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[30;101H  \u001b[97mEvery project that uses `pm` gets a `pm/qa/` directory with four\u001b[39m "]
[25.730825, "o", "                                \u001b[31;101H  \u001b[97msubdirectories of Markdown-with-frontmatter files. They feed prompts,\u001b[39m                            \u001b[32;101H  \u001b[97mthe TUI, and the CLI.\u001b[39m                                                                            \u001b[33;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[34;101H  \u001b[97m## The four directories\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[35;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[36;101H  \u001b[97m| Directory | Purpose |\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[37;101H  \u001b[97m|---|---|\u001b[39m                                                                                        \u001b[38;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/instructions/` | Reusable test-environment procedures вҖ” anything a QA scenario needs to\u001b[39m \u001b[39;101H  \u001b[97m set up before it can exercise the code (seed a da"]
[25.730834, "o", "tabase, start a dev server, prepare fixture \u001b[39m   \u001b[40;101H  \u001b[97mdata, log in a test user, etc.). Referenced by QA scenarios in their `INSTRUCTION:` field. |\u001b[39m     \u001b[41;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/regression/`   | Claude-driven test scenarios run via `pm qa regression <id>`. Each \u001b[39m    \u001b[42;101H  \u001b[97mfile is a natural-language prompt; the runner launches Claude with the prompt to exercise the \u001b[39m   \u001b[43;101H  \u001b[97mproject end-to-end and report back. |\u001b[39m                                                            \u001b[44;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/artifacts/`    | Recipes for capturing concrete evidence of behavior вҖ” recordings, \u001b[39m     \u001b[45;101H  \u001b[97mlogs, screenshots вҖ” that unambiguously confirm what happened. |\u001b[39m                                  \u001b[46;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/mocks/`        | Shared mock definitions injected verbatim into every QA scenario \u001b[39m      \u001b[47;101H  \u001b[97mprompt so\u001b[m\u000f"]
[25.730865, "o", "\u001b[40m\u001b[1;101H  \u001b[97mthe TUI, and the CLI.\u001b[39m                                                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[2;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[3;101H  \u001b[97m## The four directories\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[4;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[5;101H  \u001b[97m| Directory | Purpose |\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[6;101H  \u001b[97m|---|---|\u001b[39m                                                                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[7;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/instructions/` | Reusable test-environment procedures вҖ” anything a QA scenario needs to\u001b[39m \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[8;101H  \u001b[97m set up before it can exercise the code (seed a database, start a dev server, prepare fixture \u001b[39m   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b["]
[25.730892, "o", "40m\u001b[9;101H  \u001b[97mdata, log in a test user, etc.). Referenced by QA scenarios in their `INSTRUCTION:` field. |\u001b[39m     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[10;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/regression/`   | Claude-driven test scenarios run via `pm qa regression <id>`. Each \u001b[39m    \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[11;101H  \u001b[97mfile is a natural-language prompt; the runner launches Claude with the prompt to exercise the \u001b[39m   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[12;101H  \u001b[97mproject end-to-end and report back. |\u001b[39m                                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[13;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/artifacts/`    | Recipes for capturing concrete evidence of behavior вҖ” recordings, \u001b[39m     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[14;101H  \u001b[97mlogs, screenshots вҖ” that unambiguously confirm what happened. |\u001b[39m                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[15;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm/qa/mocks/`        | Shared mock definitions injected verbatim into every QA scenario \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[16;101H  \u001b[97mprompt so all scenarios use the same contracts for external dependencies. |\u001b[39m     "]
[25.730917, "o", "                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[17;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[18;101H  \u001b[97mThere is also a runtime sibling, `pm/qa/captures/`, written by impl,\u001b[39m                             \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[19;101H  \u001b[97mQA, and regression sessions вҖ” see [Captures](#captures) below.\u001b[39m                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[20;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[21;101H  \u001b[97m## Authoring\u001b[39m                                                                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[22;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[23;101H  \u001b[97mThere are commands available for authoring new files in Claude sessions:\u001b[39m                         \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[24;101H                                                                                                "]
[25.730939, "o", "   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[25;101H  \u001b[97m```\u001b[39m                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[26;101H  \u001b[97mpm qa author-instruction <name>     # new instruction\u001b[39m                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[27;101H  \u001b[97mpm qa author-regression <name>      # new regression test\u001b[39m                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[28;101H  \u001b[97mpm qa author-artifact <name>        # new artifact recipe\u001b[39m                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[29;101H  \u001b[97m```\u001b[39m                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[30;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[31;101H  \u001b[97mEach loads this document and walks the user through drafting the file\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[32;101H  \u001b[97mat the right path. If you'd rather just edit a stub yourself, the\u001b[39m               "]
[25.730963, "o", "                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[33;101H  \u001b[97m`pm qa add-instruction` / `add-regression` / `add-artifact` siblings\u001b[39m                             \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[34;101H  \u001b[97mscaffold a stub and open `$EDITOR`.\u001b[39m                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[35;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[36;101H  \u001b[97m## File format (instructions / regression / artifacts)\u001b[39m                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[37;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[38;101H  \u001b[97mEach `.md` file is YAML frontmatter followed by Markdown body:\u001b[39m                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[39;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[40;101H  \u001b[97m```text\u001b[39m                                                                               "]
[25.730985, "o", "           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[41;101H  \u001b[97m---\u001b[39m                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[42;101H  \u001b[97mtitle: Login flow setup\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[43;101H  \u001b[97mdescription: Seed a test user and log them in bef\u001b[39m                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[44;101H  \u001b[30mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ \u001b[37m(264 lines hidden)\u001b[30m в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[39m \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[45;101H  \u001b[97med into scenario prompts\u001b[39m                                                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[46;101H  \u001b[97m```\u001b[39m                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[47;101H                                           "]
[25.731005, "o", "                                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[48;101H  \u001b[97mReference a mock from a QA scenario by its filename stem in the\u001b[39m                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[49;101H  \u001b[97m`MOC\u001b[39m\u001b[49m\u001b[K"]
[25.731076, "o", "\u001b[40m\u001b[1;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[2;101H  \u001b[97m## File format (instructions / regression / artifacts)\u001b[39m                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[3;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[4;101H  \u001b[97mEach `.md` file is YAML frontmatter followed by Markdown body:\u001b[39m                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[5;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[6;101H  \u001b[97m```text\u001b[39m                                                                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[7;101H  \u001b[97m---\u001b[39m                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[8;101H  \u001b[97mtitle: Login flow setup\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[9;101H "]
[25.731096, "o", " \u001b[97mdescription: Seed a test user and log them in bef\u001b[39m                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[10;101H  \u001b[30mв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ \u001b[37m(264 lines hidden)\u001b[30m в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\u001b[39m \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[11;101H  \u001b[97med into scenario prompts\u001b[39m                                                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[12;101H  \u001b[97m```\u001b[39m                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[13;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[14;101H  \u001b[97mReference a mock from a QA scenario by its filename stem in the\u001b[39m                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[15;101H  \u001b[97m`MOCKS:` field (comma-separated for multiple).\u001b[39m                             "]
[25.731117, "o", "                      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[16;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[17;101H  \u001b[97m## Where each surface reads what\u001b[39m                                                                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[18;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[19;101H  \u001b[97m| Surface | What it shows / consumes |\u001b[39m                                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[20;101H  \u001b[97m|---|---|\u001b[39m                                                                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[21;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm` TUI QA pane (`q`) | Three categories listed inline (Instructions, Regression Tests, \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[22;101H  \u001b[97mArtifact Recipes); mocks have their own CLI surface via `pm qa mocks`. Reads `title`, \u001b[39m           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[23;101H  \u001b[97m`description` for display. |\u001b[39m                                           "]
[25.731136, "o", "                          \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[24;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa list` | Same three sections as the QA pane. |\u001b[39m                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[25;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa show <id>` | Full body of one file; auto-detects category. |\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[26;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa edit <id>` | Opens the file in `$EDITOR`; auto-detects category. |\u001b[39m                      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[27;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa add-instruction <name>` | Scaffolds a stub in `pm/qa/instructions/`. |\u001b[39m                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[28;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa add-regression <name>` | Scaffolds a stub in `pm/qa/regression/`. |\u001b[39m                     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[29;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa add-artifact <name>` | Scaffolds a stub in `pm/qa/artifacts/`. |\u001b[39m                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[30;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa author-instruction <name>` | Same as add-instruction, but launches a guided Claude \u001b[39m     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[31;101H  \u001b[97msession that uses this document to interview the aut"]
[25.731161, "o", "hor. |\u001b[39m                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[32;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa author-regression <name>` | Guided authoring for a regression test. |\u001b[39m                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[33;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa author-artifact <name>` | Guided authoring for an artifact recipe. |\u001b[39m                    \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[34;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa docs` | Prints this document. |\u001b[39m                                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[35;101H  \u001b[97m| QA planner prompt | `instruction_summary_for_prompt` renders `### Instructions` and `### \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[36;101H  \u001b[97mArtifact Recipes`. Recipes are referenced by filename in the scenario `INSTRUCTION:` field. |\u001b[39m    \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[37;101H  \u001b[97m| Scenario 0 prompt | Same library summary, scoped to the interactive session. |\u001b[39m                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[38;101H  \u001b[97m| Bug-fix flow prompt | Points sessions at `pm/qa/instructions/` and `pm/qa/artifacts/` by \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[39;101H  \u001b[97mdirectory; sessions discover"]
[25.731192, "o", " specific files themselves. Captures go under \u001b[39m                       \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[40;101H  \u001b[97m`pm/qa/captures/<pr-id>/impl/pre-fix/` and `вҖҰ/post-fix/`. |\u001b[39m                                      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[41;101H  \u001b[97m| Bug-fix review checklist | Tells reviewers to read captures under \u001b[39m                             \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[42;101H  \u001b[97m`pm/qa/captures/<pr-id>/impl/`. |\u001b[39m                                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[43;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa mocks list/show/add/edit` | CLI for `pm/qa/mocks/`. |\u001b[39m                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[44;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa mocks prompt` | Prints the block injected into every QA scenario prompt. |\u001b[39m              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[45;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[46;101H  \u001b[97m## Authoring tips\u001b[39m                                                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[47;101H                   "]
