[25.731631, "o", " is the most\u001b[39m                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[33;101H  \u001b[97m  load-bearing part вҖ” make it unambiguous so captures aren't opaque.\u001b[39m                             \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[34;101H  \u001b[97m- Recipes can reference your project's own paths and tooling freely вҖ”\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[35;101H  \u001b[97m  the QA library is per-project. Only extract something into a recipe\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[36;101H  \u001b[97m  if you'll reuse it across multiple scenarios or PRs.\u001b[39m                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[37;101H  \u001b[97m- `pm qa list` shows existing recipes; `pm qa show <id>` prints any\u001b[39m                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[38;101H  \u001b[97m  one of them. Browse a few before authoring something new вҖ” the\u001b[39m                                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[39;101H  \u001b[97m  fastest way to learn the shape is to read what's already there.\u001b[39m                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[40;101H                            "]
