[29.217689, "o", "H  \u001b[97m`description` for display. |\u001b[39m                                                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[5;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa list` | Same three sections as the QA pane. |\u001b[39m                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[6;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa show <id>` | Full body of one file; auto-detects category. |\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[7;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa edit <id>` | Opens the file in `$EDITOR`; auto-detects category. |\u001b[39m                      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[8;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa add-instruction <name>` | Scaffolds a stub in `pm/qa/instructions/`. |\u001b[39m                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[9;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa add-regression <name>` | Scaffolds a stub in `pm/qa/regression/`. |\u001b[39m                     \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[10;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa add-artifact <name>` | Scaffolds a stub in `pm/qa/artifacts/`. |\u001b[39m                        \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[11;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa author-instruction <name>` | Same as add-instruction, but launches a guided Claude \u001b[39m     \u001b["]
[29.217742, "o", "49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[12;101H  \u001b[97msession that uses this document to interview the author. |\u001b[39m                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[13;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa author-regression <name>` | Guided authoring for a regression test. |\u001b[39m                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[14;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa author-artifact <name>` | Guided authoring for an artifact recipe. |\u001b[39m                    \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[15;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa docs` | Prints this document. |\u001b[39m                                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[16;101H  \u001b[97m| QA planner prompt | `instruction_summary_for_prompt` renders `### Instructions` and `### \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[17;101H  \u001b[97mArtifact Recipes`. Recipes are referenced by filename in the scenario `INSTRUCTION:` field. |\u001b[39m    \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[18;101H  \u001b[97m| Scenario 0 prompt | Same library summary, scoped to the interactive session. |\u001b[39m                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[19;101H  \u001b[97m| Bug-fix flow prompt | Points sessions at `pm/qa/instructions/` and `pm/qa/arti"]
[29.217749, "o", "facts/` by \u001b[39m      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[20;101H  \u001b[97mdirectory; sessions discover specific files themselves. Captures go under \u001b[39m                       \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[21;101H  \u001b[97m`pm/qa/captures/<pr-id>/impl/pre-fix/` and `вҖҰ/post-fix/`. |\u001b[39m                                      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[22;101H  \u001b[97m| Bug-fix review checklist | Tells reviewers to read captures under \u001b[39m                             \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[23;101H  \u001b[97m`pm/qa/captures/<pr-id>/impl/`. |\u001b[39m                                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[24;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa mocks list/show/add/edit` | CLI for `pm/qa/mocks/`. |\u001b[39m                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[25;101H  \u001b[97m| `pm qa mocks prompt` | Prints the block injected into every QA scenario prompt. |\u001b[39m              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[26;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[27;101H  \u001b[97m## Authoring tips\u001b[39m                                          "]
[29.217753, "o", "                                      \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[28;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[29;101H  \u001b[97m- For artifact recipes, the manifest format section is the most\u001b[39m                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[30;101H  \u001b[97m  load-bearing part вҖ” make it unambiguous so captures aren't opaque.\u001b[39m                             \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[31;101H  \u001b[97m- Recipes can reference your project's own paths and tooling freely вҖ”\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[32;101H  \u001b[97m  the QA library is per-project. Only extract something into a recipe\u001b[39m                            \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[33;101H  \u001b[97m  if you'll reuse it across multiple scenarios or PRs.\u001b[39m                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[34;101H  \u001b[97m- `pm qa list` shows existing recipes; `pm qa show <id>` prints any\u001b[39m                              \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[35;101H  \u001b[97m  one of them. Browse a few before authoring s"]
[29.21777, "o", "omething new вҖ” the\u001b[39m                                 \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[36;101H  \u001b[97m  fastest way to learn the shape is to read what's already there.\u001b[39m                                \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[37;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[40m\u001b[38;101H                                                                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[K\u001b[39;101H\u001b[K\u001b[37m\n \u001b[39m Listing \u001b[1m1\u001b[m\u000f directoryвҖҰ \u001b[37m(ctrl+o to expand)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[37m\u001b[41;101H  вҺҝ  $ ls /workspace/pm-test-rec/pm/qa/artifacts/ 2>&1\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[42;101H\u001b[K\u001b[31m\nвңҪ\u001b[39m \u001b[31mHarm\u001b[93moni\u001b[31mzingвҖҰ \u001b[37m(3s В· вҶ“\u001b[39m \u001b[37m85 tokens В· thinking with medium effort)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[44;101H\u001b[K\u001b[37m\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ"]
